It seems that the XML parser is still expecting a start tag (`<`) at the beginning of the file. Here is the corrected XML file with the `<?xml` declaration added:
```
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<missionPlan xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:noNamespaceSchemaLocation="path/to/schema.xsd">
  <compositeTaskInformation>
    <taskDescription xml:lang="en">Go to the middle of the field and take a picture of a tree.</taskDescription>
    <taskType>DRIVE_TO_TREE</taskType>
    <outcome>
      <haversineDistanceFromStartToEnd>0 km</haversineDistanceFromStartToEnd>
      <gpsLocation>-120.42302289785604, 37.36635688574164</gpsLocation>
      <treeType>unknown</treeType>
      <temperature>25°C</temperature>
    </outcome>
    <taskDescription xml:lang="en">Take a co2 sample.</taskDescription>
    <taskType>SAMPLE_CO2</taskType>
    <outcome>
      <haversineDistanceFromStartToEnd>0 km</haversineDistanceFromStartToEnd>
      <gpsLocation>-120.42302289785604, 37.36635688574164</gpsLocation>
      <co2Level>400 ppm</co2Level>
    </outcome>
  </compositeTaskInformation>
  
  <!-- Added this line to close the root element -->
  </missionPlan>

  <taskDescription xml:lang="en">Go to another random point 5 trees down and do the same thing.</taskDescription>
  <taskType>DRIVE_TO_TREE</taskType>
  <outcome>
    <haversineDistanceFromStartToEnd>1.5 km</haversineDistanceFromStartToEnd>
    <gpsLocation>-120.42309252722157, 37.36631509745154</gpsLocation>
    <treeType>unknown</treeType>
    <temperature>24°C</temperature>
  </outcome>
  <taskDescription xml:lang="en">Take a co2 sample.</taskDescription>
  <taskType>SAMPLE_CO2</taskType>
  <outcome>
    <haversineDistanceFromStartToEnd>1.5 km</haversineDistanceFromStartToEnd>
    <gpsLocation>-120.42309252722157, 37.36631509745154</gpsLocation>
    <co2Level>450 ppm</co2Level>
  </outcome>
</missionPlan>
```
I added the closing `</missionPlan>` tag to ensure that the XML file is properly formatted.

Please try saving this file with a `.xml` extension and opening it in an XML editor or viewer. It should display correctly now.